17 (2) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
18 the O.C.G.A., as amended.
19 (b) Each resident of Lowndes County who is 65 years of age or older on or before January 1
20 of the year in which application for the exemption required by subsection (d) of this section
21 is made is granted an exemption on such person's homestead from Lowndes County ad
22 valorem taxes for county purposes in the amount of $40,000.00 of the assessed value of such
23 homestead. The value of that property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain
24 subject to taxation.
25 (c) Each resident of Lowndes County who is 70 years of age or older on or before January 1
26 of the year in which application for the exemption required by subsection (d) of this section
27 is made is granted an exemption on such person's homestead from Lowndes County ad
28 valorem taxes for county purposes in the amount of $50,000.00 of the assessed value of such
29 homestead. The value of that property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain
30 subject to taxation.
31 (d)(1) Except as provided for in paragraph (2) of this subsection, a person shall not
32 receive the homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) or (c) of this section unless
33 such person or person's agent files an application with the tax commissioner of Lowndes
34 County, giving such information relative to receiving such exemption as will enable the
35 tax commissioner of Lowndes County to make a determination regarding the initial and
36 continuing eligibility of such person for such exemption. The tax commissioner of
37 Lowndes County shall provide application forms for this purpose.
38 (2) Each resident of Lowndes County 65 years of age or older allowed the $10,000.00
39 homestead exemption on such resident's homestead from Lowndes County ad valorem
40 taxes for county purposes granted by the amendment to the Constitution of the State of
41 Georgia applicable to residents of Lowndes County adopted by Ga. Laws 1980, p. 2207,
42 shall be automatically allowed the exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section
