43 without filing an application with the tax commissioner of Lowndes County as provided
44 in paragraph (1) of this subsection.
45 (e) The exemption shall be claimed and returned as provided in Code Section 48-5-50.1 of
46 the O.C.G.A., as amended. The exemption shall be automatically renewed from year to year
47 so long as the person granted the homestead exemption under subsection (b) or (c) of this
48 section occupies the residence as a homestead. After such person has filed the proper
49 application as provided in paragraph (1) of subsection (d) of this section or is automatically
50 allowed the exemption granted by subsection (b) of this Code section as provided for in
51 paragraph (2) of subsection (d) of this Code section, it shall not be necessary to make
52 application thereafter for any year, and such exemption shall continue to be allowed to such
53 person. It shall be the duty of any such person granted the homestead exemption under
54 subsection (b) or (c) of this section to notify the tax commissioner of Lowndes County in the
55 event that such person for any reason becomes ineligible for such exemption.
56 (f)(1) The exemption granted by subsection (b) or (c) of this section shall not apply to
57 or affect any state ad valorem taxes, county or independent school district ad valorem
58 taxes for educational purposes, or municipal ad valorem taxes for municipal purposes.
59 (2) The homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section shall be in lieu
60 of and not in addition to any other homestead exemption applicable to Lowndes County
61 ad valorem taxes for county purposes, including but not limited to the exemption granted
62 in subsection (c) of this section.
63 (3) The homestead exemption granted by subsection (c) of this section shall be in lieu
64 of and not in addition to any other homestead exemption applicable to Lowndes County
65 ad valorem taxes for county purposes, including but not limited to the exemption granted
66 in subsection (b) of this section.
67 (g) The exemption granted by subsection (b) or (c) of this section shall apply to all taxable
68 years beginning on or after January 1, 2027.
